<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There are great players out there who are not uber, who play their class well and have solid equipment and are not uber who deserve to play in the new planes. I think it's pretty sad actually that some of the people posting here have the attitude like, &quot;If you cant pass the trials then you don't belong in the new planes&quot;. That's the stupidest thing I ever heard.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well, VI decided that when they can complete one of these six trials then they deserve to enter Storms/Valor - noone here had a say in that decision. VI has a long line of testing people before entering certain zones - Sebilis, Charasis, Veeshan's Peaks, Sleeper's Tomb, certain areas of Ssra, Vex Thal - what's all different from the trials is that you can bring an unlimited number to try and get these keys, not so with the trials where you have to rely on six people and a combination of level, gear, aa-skills, tactics/ingenuity and luck.<br>
<br>
I was extremely impressed by a recent applicant to our guild, don't think he was ever guilded before - yet he managed to not only get flags to PoS/PoV, he even got the box of souls for HoH and everything but a desert/forest medallion for the BoT key, this tells me that where there's a will and determination there is a way - this BST found a way.<br>
<br>
