<br>
Very good lessons.  And some are things that people from a raiding guild would have assumed from the get go, just because they become second nature.  Assist key, permenant feature on my hotkey bank, I'd assume it would be that way for anyone who raided regularly.  Limiting ping ponging, big deal on a raid, you learn this or you wipe.<br>
<br>
The only one that I would say is really new is the fact you have to target the mobs one after another very very quickly, no hesistation, no doubts, just do it.<br>
<br>
In no way is this meant to be a negative commentary on anyone, but one factor we probably hadn't considered that makes the trials easier for members of a guild is most members will have learned certain techniques that not all non-raiding people will have learned.  And they can make a big difference. <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
