It still got close a couple times. Due to lack of communication, Cleric and I died on Executioner the first time. The Ranger got flagged but I did not. I was very happy the rogue was willing to stay for another try for me.<br>
<br>
I will say one thing. I have ALWAYS believed there were multiple ways to get something done. I have helped out people's alts, run Hole raids for young shamans who couldn't do it at the time and grew up into level 60 Malo and Torpor monsters owing me favors, same with paladins and rangers and chanters on those same raids.<br>
<br>
The 65 rogue that helped me is just someone who appreciated my point of view on a message board on a sticky issue and we kept in touch in-game.<br>
<br>
Do your homework. Get a really solid crew together and then ask ONE person from a high-end guild if they would like to help you. Explain the amount of work you have put into making sure that you don't waste their time.<br>
<br>
Don't try and form pick-up groups sitting on the platform in PoJ.<br>
<br>
There is a reason all those people are still sitting there.<br>
<br>
Find a way that someone would want to help you. There are about a million of them out there.<br>
<br>
It never hurts to ask. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iiowyn>Iiowyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/8/02 2:24:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2567.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I HATE the Trials...</span><hr size=1> gratz jakle =)<br>
