Only one death on failed attempt, 2 on successful one while first engaging exe.<br>
First six tries were<br>
61 warrior (myself with ND 2, no AE taunt back then)<br>
61 cleric <br>
61 enchanter<br>
60 druid<br>
60 shaman<br>
63 rogue<br>
<br>
None of us had even 20 AA's back then.<br>
It was usually very close, one second in 4th wave as best then we changed and replaced the druid with a 61 monk (also less than 20 aa's) and succeeded first try.<br>
<br>
Our tactic: I stand in the middle and engage first mob spawning close to me.<br>
Chanter moves close to me and AE stuns with color series.<br>
Shaman AE slows till most of them are slowed then nukes and melees (plus pet).<br>
Cleric melees like crazy with 60 hammer (proc machine) and only uses fast spot heals (supernatural remedy).<br>
<br>
Things to consider: <br>
Chanter had arcane rune available and reruned between waves<br>
Shaman had JBB, so fast (though not hard damage) nukes.<br>
<br>
Equipent was about average I'd say with the cleric having a mana pool &gt; 4000, and me sporting past 4k hp unbuffed even then (2 and a half weeks ago).<br>
